      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "I’m back with a Travel with Me: Weekend Edition post, a shortened version of my "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/category/travel-with-me/",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "Travel With Me"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " posts. These posts are for trips that are just a weekend or a long weekend – I share what we did, what we ate, and where we stayed with short descriptions. I hope that these posts can help you plan a short trip yourself or at least inspire you to visit a new place!"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "[caption id=\"attachment_3927\" align=\"alignnone\" width=\"1024\"]"
          },
          {
            "type": "image",
            "attrs": {
              "src": "images/BIRU-WP-141.jpeg",
              "alt": "BIRU-WP-141.jpeg",
              "title": null
            },
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "http://www.everydayaccountsblog.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/11/BIRU-WP-141.jpeg",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " View of Burlington, VT[/caption]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For this post, I’m sharing our four-day trip to Vermont mid-November of this year. We both love New England and had been wanting to get away from the big city for a few days, so Vermont seemed like the perfect place to go."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 1
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "strong"
              }
            ],
            "text": "Where We Stayed:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "We used AirBnB for the first time on this trip. While searching for lodging options online, I ran across "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/225948",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "this listing"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " and knew this was our place to stay. For $89 each night, you could not ask for a more perfect place to relax and enjoy the Vermont countryside. The owner, Christine, welcomed us with pastries just minutes after we pulled in for our stay. Each morning we woke up to a panorama of mountains through the windows; one morning we woke up to snow falling and felt like we were in a snow globe! We requested to have breakfast brought to our room one morning, and it was a fantastic assortment of pancakes, eggs, sausage, and smoothies all made from locally-sourced ingredients."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The rental is located fifteen minutes from Bristol, VT, a quaint little town with great dining options. Additionally, it is located one hour from Burlington, a much more populous area with many shops and restaurants to choose from. While it is a bit of a long drive to get out of the countryside, our focus for this trip was to NOT have every minute of every day planned (as we usually do), so staying in the country really encouraged us to take that slower pace. We loved our stay at Christine's barn. I give the rental a rating of "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "strong"
              }
            ],
            "text": "5 out of 5"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". You should "
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "link",
                "attrs": {
                  "href": "https://www.airbnb.com/rooms/225948",
                  "title": null
                }
              }
            ],
            "text": "check it out"
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " if you are looking for a New England escape!"
          }
        ]
      },
